ne 896: python -c \"from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient; print('Import successful')\"\n  Line 929: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n  Line 957:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n  Line 983:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n  Line 1012:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n  Line 1063: \"\"\"Basic AgentRuntimeClient usage example.\"\"\"\n  Line 1065: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n  Line 1071:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n  Line 1091: \"\"\"AgentRuntimeClient session reuse example.\"\"\"\n  Line 1093: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n  Line 1098:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n  Line 1122: \"\"\"AgentRuntimeClient custom timeout example.\"\"\"\n  Line 1124: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n  Line 1130:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n  Line 1156: git commit -m \"docs(ar-028): add usage examples for AgentRuntimeClient\"\n  Line 1167: **Step 1: Create AgentRuntimeClient documentation**\n  Line 1170: # AgentRuntimeClient Documentation\n  Line 1172: The AgentRuntimeClient provides a high-level interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service.\n  Line 1183: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n  Line 1185: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n  Line 1215: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n  Line 1219: Initialize the AgentRuntimeClient.\n  Line 1254: client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n  Line 1264: client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n  Line 1275: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n  Line 1278:     with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\") as client:\n  Line 1296: Add section about AgentRuntimeClient to README.md.\n  Line 1302: git commit -m \"docs(ar-028): update AgentRuntimeClient documentation\"\n  Line 1354: Add entry for AR-028 implementation.\n  Line 1367: This implementation plan breaks down AR-028 (SDK AgentRuntimeClient) into 15 atomic, independently verifiable tasks:\n  Line 1369: 1. **Verify AgentRuntimeClient class structure** - Ensure all required methods and attributes exist\n  Line 1370: 2. **Verify AgentRuntimeClient initialization** - Test all constructor parameters and defaults\n  Line 1392: - AgentRuntimeClient provides a simple, intuitive API\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design Document\n  Line 5: This design document outlines the architecture and implementation approach for the AgentRuntimeClient, a Python SDK client that provides a high-level interface for managing agents and their runtime sessions. The AgentRuntimeClient enables users to invoke agent workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 197 matches (97 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":197,"truncated":true},"title":"AR-028|AgentRuntimeClient","time":{"start":1775879115681,"end":1775879115693}}}}
