{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879127107,"sessionID":"ses_2855b39bdffecO2fXIunWqEVjF","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa500400013a9gPUBacbJExW","messageID":"msg_d7aa4fb6a0013ZSQPa9Hjc3Ndj","sessionID":"ses_2855b39bdffecO2fXIunWqEVjF","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879128671,"sessionID":"ses_2855b39bdffecO2fXIunWqEVjF","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa503c6001zvB4vnXF6GGHeY","messageID":"msg_d7aa4fb6a0013ZSQPa9Hjc3Ndj","sessionID":"ses_2855b39bdffecO2fXIunWqEVjF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ca894c4f2ce641b4abcc2b872871a0ce","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This delta specification extends the base AgentCube Python SDK specifications for the `AgentRuntimeClient` component, providing additional acceptance criteria for edge cases, error handling, and configuration scenarios.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Router URL configuration validation\n10: \n11: The system SHALL validate that a router URL is available either via argument or environment variable.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Router URL missing at initialization\n14: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n15: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` is called\n16: - **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning message about ROUTER_URL not being set\n17: - **AND** the system SHALL set `self.router_url` to an empty string\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Router URL provided via argument\n20: - **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router.example.com\"` is provided to `__init__`\n21: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n22: - **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set to `\"http://router.example.com\"`\n23: - **AND** no warning SHALL be logged\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n26: - **GIVEN** environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set to `\"http://env-router.example.com\"`\n27: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` is called without `router_url` argument\n28: - **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set to `\"http://env-router.example.com\"`\n29: \n30: ### Requirement: Session ID bootstrap and reuse\n31: \n32: The system SHALL support both bootstrapping a new session ID from the router and reusing an existing session ID.\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Bootstrap new session ID on initialization\n35: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided to `__init__`\n36: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n37: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `bootstrap_session_id()` on the data plane client\n38: - **AND** `self.session_id` SHALL be set to the bootstrapped session ID\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Reuse existing session ID\n41: - **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-123\"` is provided to `__init__`\n42: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n43: - **THEN** the system SHALL NOT call `bootstrap_session_id()`\n44: - **AND** `self.session_id` SHALL be set to `\"existing-session-123\"`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID missing response header\n47: - **GIVEN** the router returns a response without the `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n48: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n49: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID network failure\n52: - **GIVEN** the router is unreachable or returns an error status\n53: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n54: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `requests.RequestException`\n55: - **AND** the initialization SHALL fail\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: Invoke method with session validation\n58: \n59: The system SHALL validate that a session ID is initialized before allowing invoke operations.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Invoke with initialized session\n62: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is initialized\n63: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"input\": \"test\"})` is called\n64: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST the payload to the data plane endpoint\n65: - **AND** return the response JSON\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Invoke without session ID\n68: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty string\n69: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"input\": \"test\"})` is called\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized`\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Invoke with per-call timeout override\n73: - **GIVEN** default instance timeout is `120` seconds\n74: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={}, timeout=30.0)` is called\n75: - **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `30.0` seconds\n76: - **AND** the connect timeout SHALL remain the instance default\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Invoke without per-call timeout\n79: - **GIVEN** instance timeout is `120` seconds and instance connect_timeout is `5.0` seconds\n80: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={}, timeout=None)` is called\n81: - **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n82: \n83: ### Requirement: Context manager lifecycle\n84: \n85: The system SHALL support the context manager protocol for proper resource cleanup.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Context manager enter\n88: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n89: - **WHEN** entering the context (`with AgentRuntimeClient(...) as client:`)\n90: - **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Context manager exit on normal completion\n93: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n94: - **WHEN** the context block exits normally\n95: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` on the client\n96: - **AND** the underlying HTTP session SHALL be closed\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Context manager exit on exception\n99: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n100: - **WHEN** the context block exits due to an exception\n101: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` on the client\n102: - **AND** the underlying HTTP session SHALL be closed\n103: - **AND** the exception SHALL propagate normally\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Data plane client initialization\n106: \n107: The system SHALL properly initialize the data plane client with the correct configuration.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Data plane client receives correct parameters\n110: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`\n111: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n112: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL be instantiated with the same `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`\n113: - **AND** the data plane client SHALL construct the correct base URL using `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Data plane client default connection pool settings\n116: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized without custom pool settings\n117: - **WHEN** the data plane client is created\n118: - **THEN** `pool_connections` SHALL default to `10`\n119: - **AND** `pool_maxsize` SHALL default to `10`\n120: \n121: ### Requirement: HTTP session management\n122: \n123: The system SHALL properly manage the underlying HTTP session lifecycle.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Close method closes HTTP session\n126: - **GIVEN** an initialized `AgentRuntimeClient`\n127: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n128: - **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed\n129: - **AND** an info log message SHALL be logged\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Data plane close method\n132: - **GIVEN** an initialized `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n133: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n134: - **THEN** the `requests.Session` SHALL be closed\n135: - **AND** a debug log message SHALL be logged\n136: \n137: ### Requirement: Verbose logging configuration\n138: \n139: The system SHALL support verbose logging for debugging purposes.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Verbose logging enabled\n142: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True` is passed to `__init__`\n143: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n144: - **THEN** the logger level SHALL be set to `DEBUG` (level 10)\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Verbose logging disabled\n147: - **GIVEN** `verbose=False` is passed to `__init__` or omitted\n148: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n149: - **THEN** the logger level SHALL remain at the default `INFO` level\n150: \n151: ### Requirement: Session header management\n152: \n153: The system SHALL consistently use the `x-agentcube-session-id` header for all Router requests.\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Session header constant\n156: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n157: - **WHEN** accessing the session header name\n158: - **THEN** `SESSION_HEADER` SHALL be set to `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Invoke includes session header\n161: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called with a valid `session_id`\n162: - **WHEN** the POST request is made\n163: - **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: Error handling and propagation\n166: \n167: The system SHALL properly handle and propagate errors from HTTP requests.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Invoke on non-2xx response\n170: - **GIVEN** the router returns a status code >= 400\n171: - **WHEN** `invoke()` is called\n172: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `response.raise_for_status()`\n173: - **AND** `requests.HTTPError` SHALL be raised\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Bootstrap on non-2xx response\n176: - **GIVEN** the router returns a status code >= 400 during bootstrap\n177: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n178: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `response.raise_for_status()`\n179: - **AND** `requests.HTTPError` SHALL be raised\n180: \n181: ### Requirement: Type annotations and API contract\n182: \n183: The system SHALL provide proper type annotations for public methods.\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Type annotations present\n186: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` classes\n187: - **WHEN** inspecting method signatures\n188: - **THEN** `__init__` SHALL have proper type annotations\n189: - **AND** `__enter__` SHALL return `\"AgentRuntimeClient\"`\n190: - **AND** `invoke` SHALL accept `payload: dict[str, object]` and `timeout: float | None`\n191: - **AND** `invoke` SHALL return `dict[str, object]`\n192: - **AND** `close` SHALL return `None`\n193: \n194: ---\n195: \n196: ## Backward Compatibility\n197: \n198: This delta specification extends the existing base specifications for the AgentRuntimeClient. All requirements are additive and do not modify existing behavior. The implementation remains fully backward compatible with code that uses the AgentRuntimeClient according to the base design and specification documents.\n199: \n200: ## Dependencies\n201: \n202: This delta specification depends on:\n203: - Base design document: `python-sdk/design.md`\n204: - Base specification document: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n205: - Python >= 3.10 (as specified in base requirements)\n206: - `requests` library (as specified in base requirements)\n207: \n208: ## Breaking Changes\n209: \n210: None. This delta specification defines additional acceptance criteria for the existing AgentRuntimeClient implementation without introducing breaking changes.\n\n(End of file - total 210 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification extends the base AgentCube Python SDK specifications for the `AgentRuntimeClient` component, providing additional acceptance criteria for edge cases, error handling, and configuration scenarios.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Router URL configuration validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that a router URL is available either via argument or environment variable.\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL missing at initialization\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning message about ROUTER_URL not being set\n- **AND** the system SHALL set `self.router_url` to an empty string\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL provided via argument\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router.example.com\"` is provided to `__init__`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879128657,"end":1775879128669}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879128674,"sessionID":"ses_2855b39bdffecO2fXIunWqEVjF","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa50638001hJqYk8znc8DVS9","messageID":"msg_d7aa4fb6a0013ZSQPa9Hjc3Ndj","sessionID":"ses_2855b39bdffecO2fXIunWqEVjF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ec4a35959c1041c09d98723965e00a1b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Specification\n2: \n3: ## Module: sdk-python\n4: \n5: ### AgentRuntimeClient Class\n6: \n7: #### Constructor\n8: \n9: ```python\n10: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n11:     def __init__(\n12:         self,\n13:         base_url: str,\n14:         api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n15:         timeout: int = 30,\n16:         max_retries: int = 3\n17:     ) -> None\n18: ```\n19: \n20: **Parameters:**\n21: - `base_url`: Base URL of the AgentRuntime service\n22: - `api_key`: Optional API key for authentication\n23: - `timeout`: Request timeout in seconds (default: 30)\n24: - `max_retries`: Maximum number of retry attempts (default: 3)\n25: \n26: #### Agent Management Methods\n27: \n28: ##### create_agent\n29: \n30: ```python\n31: async def create_agent(\n32:     self,\n33:     config: AgentConfig,\n34:     workspace_id: Optional[str] = None\n35: ) -> Agent\n36: ```\n37: \n38: **Parameters:**\n39: - `config`: Agent configuration object\n40: - `workspace_id`: Optional workspace ID\n41: \n42: **Returns:** `Agent` object\n43: \n44: **Raises:** `AgentCreationError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`, `ValidationError`\n45: \n46: ##### get_agent\n47: \n48: ```python\n49: async def get_agent(self, agent_id: str) -> Agent\n50: ```\n51: \n52: **Parameters:**\n53: - `agent_id`: ID of the agent\n54: \n55: **Returns:** `Agent` object\n56: \n57: **Raises:** `AgentNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n58: \n59: ##### list_agents\n60: \n61: ```python\n62: async def list_agents(\n63:     self,\n64:     workspace_id: Optional[str] = None,\n65:     status: Optional[AgentStatus] = None,\n66:     limit: int = 100,\n67:     offset: int = 0\n68: ) -> List[Agent]\n69: ```\n70: \n71: **Parameters:**\n72: - `workspace_id`: Optional workspace ID to filter by\n73: - `status`: Optional agent status to filter by\n74: - `limit`: Maximum number of agents to return (default: 100)\n75: - `offset`: Pagination offset (default: 0)\n76: \n77: **Returns:** List of `Agent` objects\n78: \n79: **Raises:** `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n80: \n81: ##### update_agent\n82: \n83: ```python\n84: async def update_agent(\n85:     self,\n86:     agent_id: str,\n87:     config: AgentConfig\n88: ) -> Agent\n89: ```\n90: \n91: **Parameters:**\n92: - `agent_id`: ID of the agent\n93: - `config`: Updated agent configuration\n94: \n95: **Returns:** Updated `Agent` object\n96: \n97: **Raises:** `AgentNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`, `ValidationError`\n98: \n99: ##### delete_agent\n100: \n101: ```python\n102: async def delete_agent(self, agent_id: str) -> None\n103: ```\n104: \n105: **Parameters:**\n106: - `agent_id`: ID of the agent\n107: \n108: **Raises:** `AgentNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n109: \n110: #### Runtime Operations Methods\n111: \n112: ##### start_agent\n113: \n114: ```python\n115: async def start_agent(\n116:     self,\n117:     agent_id: str,\n118:     input_data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n119: ) -> RuntimeSession\n120: ```\n121: \n122: **Parameters:**\n123: - `agent_id`: ID of the agent\n124: - `input_data`: Optional input data for the agent\n125: \n126: **Returns:** `RuntimeSession` object\n127: \n128: **Raises:** `AgentNotFoundError`, `RuntimeError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n129: \n130: ##### stop_agent\n131: \n132: ```python\n133: async def stop_agent(\n134:     self,\n135:     session_id: str,\n136:     graceful: bool = True\n137: ) -> None\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Parameters:**\n141: - `session_id`: ID of the runtime session\n142: - `graceful`: Whether to stop gracefully (default: True)\n143: \n144: **Raises:** `SessionNotFoundError`, `RuntimeError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n145: \n146: ##### get_session_status\n147: \n148: ```python\n149: async def get_session_status(self, session_id: str) -> RuntimeSession\n150: ```\n151: \n152: **Parameters:**\n153: - `session_id`: ID of the runtime session\n154: \n155: **Returns:** `RuntimeSession` object\n156: \n157: **Raises:** `SessionNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n158: \n159: ##### list_sessions\n160: \n161: ```python\n162: async def list_sessions(\n163:     self,\n164:     agent_id: Optional[str] = None,\n165:     status: Optional[SessionStatus] = None,\n166:     limit: int = 100,\n167:     offset: int = 0\n168: ) -> List[RuntimeSession]\n169: ```\n170: \n171: **Parameters:**\n172: - `agent_id`: Optional agent ID to filter by\n173: - `status`: Optional session status to filter by\n174: - `limit`: Maximum number of sessions to return (default: 100)\n175: - `offset`: Pagination offset (default: 0)\n176: \n177: **Returns:** List of `RuntimeSession` objects\n178: \n179: **Raises:** `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n180: \n181: ## Data Models\n182: \n183: ### Agent\n184: \n185: ```python\n186: class Agent(BaseModel):\n187:     agent_id: str\n188:     workspace_id: str\n189:     name: str\n190:     description: Optional[str]\n191:     config: AgentConfig\n192:     status: AgentStatus  # Enum: CREATING, ACTIVE, STOPPED, ERROR, DELETED\n193:     created_at: datetime\n194:     updated_at: datetime\n195:     metadata: Dict[str, str]\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### AgentStatus\n199: \n200: ```python\n201: class AgentStatus(str, Enum):\n202:     CREATING = \"creating\"\n203:     ACTIVE = \"active\"\n204:     STOPPED = \"stopped\"\n205:     ERROR = \"error\"\n206:     DELETED = \"deleted\"\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ### AgentConfig\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: class AgentConfig(BaseModel):\n213:     runtime_config: RuntimeConfig\n214:     capabilities: List[str]\n215:     constraints: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n216:     resources: Optional[ResourceConfig] = None\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### RuntimeConfig\n220: \n221: ```python\n222: class RuntimeConfig(BaseModel):\n223:     type: str  # e.g., \"llm\", \"function\", \"hybrid\"\n224:     model_id: str\n225:     parameters: Dict[str, Any]\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ### ResourceConfig\n229: \n230: ```python\n231: class ResourceConfig(BaseModel):\n232:     cpu: Optional[str] = None\n233:     memory: Optional[str] = None\n234:     gpu: Optional[str] = None\n235:     timeout: Optional[int] = None\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### RuntimeSession\n239: \n240: ```python\n241: class RuntimeSession(BaseModel):\n242:     session_id: str\n243:     agent_id: str\n244:     status: SessionStatus  # Enum: STARTING, RUNNING, COMPLETED, STOPPED, ERROR\n245:     input_data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n246:     output_data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n247:     started_at: datetime\n248:     completed_at: Optional[datetime] = None\n249:     error_message: Optional[str] = None\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### SessionStatus\n253: \n254: ```python\n255: class SessionStatus(str, Enum):\n256:     STARTING = \"starting\"\n257:     RUNNING = \"running\"\n258:     COMPLETED = \"completed\"\n259:     STOPPED = \"stopped\"\n260:     ERROR = \"error\"\n261: ```\n262: \n263: ## Exception Hierarchy\n264: \n265: ```\n266: AgentRuntimeException\n267: ├── AuthenticationError\n268: ├── ConnectionError\n269: ├── AgentError\n270: │   ├── AgentCreationError\n271: │   ├── AgentNotFoundError\n272: │   └── AgentUpdateError\n273: ├── RuntimeError\n274: │   ├── SessionNotFoundError\n275: │   └── RuntimeError as ExecutionError\n276: └── ValidationError\n277: ```\n278: \n279: ## HTTP Endpoints\n280: \n281: ### Agent Endpoints\n282: \n283: - `POST /v1/agents` - Create agent\n284: - `GET /v1/agents/{agent_id}` - Get agent\n285: - `GET /v1/agents` - List agents\n286: - `PUT /v1/agents/{agent_id}` - Update agent\n287: - `DELETE /v1/agents/{agent_id}` - Delete agent\n288: \n289: ### Runtime Endpoints\n290: \n291: - `POST /v1/agents/{agent_id}/start` - Start agent\n292: - `POST /v1/sessions/{session_id}/stop` - Stop agent\n293: - `GET /v1/sessions/{session_id}` - Get session status\n294: - `GET /v1/sessions` - List sessions\n\n(End of file - total 294 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Specification\n\n## Module: sdk-python\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient Class\n\n#### Constructor\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        base_url: str,\n        api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 30,\n        max_retries: int = 3\n    ) -> None\n```\n\n**Parameters:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/spec.md","time":{"start":1775879128660,"end":1775879128671}}}}
